162
00:10:32,672 --> 00:10:34,033
to the extent that we didn't notice,

163
00:10:34,473 --> 00:10:36,554
or at least if we noticed, we didn't resent

164
00:10:37,554 --> 00:10:39,835
the hand of the author guiding us along.

165
00:10:43,957 --> 00:10:46,078
If on the other hand, you feel that the story

166
00:10:46,138 --> 00:10:49,080
is reducing your sense of authorship over the experience,

167
00:10:49,800 --> 00:10:51,941
the mechanics of the game are at odds

168
00:10:52,181 --> 00:10:54,022
with what the authored experience is trying to convey.

169
00:10:55,092 --> 00:10:57,153
Well, you end up with a dissonance

170
00:10:57,473 --> 00:10:59,095
that can ruin any sense of immersion

171
00:10:59,695 --> 00:11:01,216
you might have otherwise experienced.

172
00:11:02,277 --> 00:11:03,338
And even though you may not be able

173
00:11:03,358 --> 00:11:04,739
