174
00:11:04,759 --> 00:11:07,641
the game just won't feel right.

175
00:11:09,763 --> 00:11:11,644
The challenge in providing authored story

176
00:11:11,684 --> 00:11:14,326
as a framework over a game that is heavily biased

177
00:11:14,487 --> 00:11:18,330
towards player experimentation of the gameplay space,

178
00:11:19,170 --> 00:11:21,272
which is the definition of a sandbox survival game,

179
00:11:22,267 --> 00:11:23,387
is in striking the balance

180
00:11:23,808 --> 00:11:25,229
between the different types of story

181
00:11:25,569 --> 00:11:26,609
the player will experience.

182
00:11:33,854 --> 00:11:35,976
In The Long Dark, players experience story

183
00:11:35,996 --> 00:11:37,196
across a variety of layers.

184
00:11:38,237 --> 00:11:39,438
Each of these layers is supported

185
00:11:39,478 --> 00:11:41,859
by a kind of narrative scaffolding

186
00:11:42,640 --> 00:11:46,382
that is comprised of all the things you see, hear, do,

187
00:11:47,023 --> 00:11:48,784
and feel as you go through the game.

188
00:11:50,655 --> 00:11:52,895
This is just an opinion, but I feel that players,

189
00:11:53,255 --> 00:11:54,356
I believe that players who feel good

190
00:11:54,376 --> 00:11:55,876
about their experiences in the long dark

191
00:11:57,897 --> 00:12:00,357
